== Overview == Yuki-no-Mikura is located in Ujikan-chō, {{ill|Ise, Mie|ja|伊勢市|12=draft}}, within the precincts of the Inner Shrine. It is ranked 7th among the 30 shrines under the jurisdiction of the Inner Shrine. The term "Yuki" (由貴) in its name means "pure and free from defilement."<ref name="gk">Gakken Publishing (2013): p. 56</ref>
Yuki-no-Mikura was originally a storehouse for offering sacred provisions ({{ill|minie|ja|御贄|12=draft}}) used in the {{ill|Yuki-no-Ōmike|ja|由貴大御饌|12=draft}} ceremony.<ref name="ic"/><ref name="gk"/> The former shrine building served as a temporary main hall for {{ill|Yodo Shrine|ja|與杼神社|12=draft}} in {{ill|Fushimi-ku, Kyoto|ja|伏見区|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都市|12=draft}}, after the shrine was destroyed by fire, from 1975 (Shōwa 50) to 1979 (Shōwa 54).<ref>Yodo Shrine, "[http://www.yodojinja.com/yodojinja/syaden.html About the Shrine - Yodo Shrine, Guardian of Fushimi, Kyoto]" (Accessed October 13, 2013)</ref>
The shrine building is surrounded by a {{ill|tamagaki|ja|玉垣|12=draft}} (sacred fence). There is no {{ill|saisenbako|ja|賽銭箱|12=draft}} (offering box).
The enshrined deity is Yuki-no-Mikura-no-Kami (由貴御倉神), who serves as the guardian deity of Yuki-no-Mikura.<ref name="ic"/><ref name="gk"/>
== Access == ; To Uji Bridge * About 15 minutes by {{ill|Mie Kotsu|ja|三重交通|12=draft}} bus from the south exit of {{ill|Ise-shi Station|ja|伊勢市駅|12=draft}} (JR side) on the {{ill|Sangū Line|ja|参宮線|12=draft}} or from {{ill|Ujiyamada Station|ja|宇治山田駅|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Kintetsu Yamada Line|ja|近鉄山田線|12=draft}}/{{ill|Kintetsu Toba Line|ja|近鉄鳥羽線|12=draft}}. Get off at the "Naikū-mae" bus stop (final stop).<ref name="mkr">Mie Prefecture Tourism Federation, "[http://www.kankomie.or.jp/spot/detail_2937.html Ise Grand Shrine (Inner Shrine) Information - Visit Mie]" (Accessed October 12, 2013)</ref> * Alternatively, from {{ill|Isuzugawa Station|ja|五十鈴川駅|12=draft}} on the Kintetsu Toba Line, take a Mie Kotsu bus to Naikū-mae. * About 5 minutes south via {{ill|Mie Prefectural Route 32|ja|三重県道32号伊勢磯部線|12=draft}} (Omikemichi) from {{ill|Ise-nishi IC|ja|伊勢西インターチェンジ|12=draft}} on the {{ill|Ise Expressway|ja|伊勢自動車道|12=draft}}, or about 5 minutes south via {{ill|National Route 23|ja|国道23号|12=draft}} from {{ill|Ise IC|ja|伊勢インターチェンジ|12=draft}}. Parking is available nearby.<ref name="mkr"/>
; From Uji Bridge * From Uji Bridge, proceed along the approach path towards the Inner Shrine (Main Shrine), and you will find the Gojōden.<ref name="ic"/> Two subordinate shrines are located to the north: Yuki-no-Mikura is on the right, and {{ill|Misakadono-no-Kami|ja|御酒殿神|12=draft}} is on the left.<ref name="ic"/><ref name="gk"/> Nearby is the sacred site of {{ill|Yotsuishi-no-Kami|ja|四至神|1=Miyanomeguri-no-Kami|12=draft}}.<ref name="ic"/>
