{{infobox Shinto shrine |name= Yuki-no-Mikura |religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image= [[File:Yuki no Mikura 2.jpg|270px]] |location= {{ill|Ujikan-chō|ja|宇治館町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ujikan-chō|qq=}} 1, [[:en:Ise, Mie|Ise, Mie]], [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]], within the precincts of the {{ill|Kōtai Jingū|ja|皇大神宮|1=Kōtai Jingū|2=ja|3=皇大神宮|4=zh|5=皇大神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|qq=}} |latitude_deg = 34 |latitude_min = 27 |latitude_sec = 19.5 |longitude_deg = 136 |longitude_min = 43 |longitude_sec = 26.6 |map= Japan Mie |enshrined_deity= Yuki-no-Mikura-no-Kami |status= {{ill|Kōtai Jingū|ja|皇大神宮|1=Kōtai Jingū|2=ja|3=皇大神宮|4=zh|5=皇大神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|qq=}} subordinate shrine |established= Before [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] 23 (804) |main_hall_style= [[Yuiitsu Shinmei-zukuri]] |alternate_names= |sacred_sites= |annual_festival= |rituals= [[:en:Kannamesai Festival|Kannamesai]] }}
'''Yuki-no-Mikura''' (由貴御倉) is a subordinate shrine of {{ill|Ise Grand Shrine (Inner Shrine)|ja|皇大神宮|1=Kōtai Jingū|2=ja|3=皇大神宮|4=zh|5=皇大神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ise Grand Shrine (Inner Shrine)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|qq=}} (Kōtai Jingū). It is also referred to as '''Yuki-no-Mikura-no-Kami''' (由貴御倉神).<ref name="ic">Ise Bunka-sha (2008): p. 115</ref><ref>Ujiyamada City Office (1929): p. 16</ref><ref name="gs2">Sakurai (1970): p. 156</ref> It is located within the precincts of the Inner Shrine, standing north of the {{ill|Gojōden|ja|五丈殿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gojōden|qq=}}, alongside {{ill|Misakadono-no-Kami|ja|御酒殿神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Misakadono-no-Kami|qq=}}.<ref name="ic"/>
== Overview == Yuki-no-Mikura is located in Ujikan-chō, [[:en:Ise, Mie|Ise, Mie]], within the precincts of the Inner Shrine. It is Ranked 7th among the 30 shrines under the jurisdiction of the Inner Shrine. The term "Yuki" (由貴) in its name means "pure and free from defilement."<ref name="gk">Gakken Publishing (2013): p. 56</ref>
Yuki-no-Mikura was originally a storehouse for offering sacred provisions ({{ill|minie|ja|御贄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/minie|qq=}}) used in the {{ill|Yuki-no-Ōmike|ja|由貴大御饌|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yuki-no-Ōmike|qq=}} ceremony.<ref name="ic"/><ref name="gk"/> The former shrine building served as a temporary main hall for {{ill|Yodo Shrine|ja|與杼神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yodo Shrine|qq=}} in [[:en:Fushimi-ku, Kyoto|Fushimi-ku, Kyoto]], [[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto]], after the shrine was destroyed by fire, from 1975 (Shōwa 50) to 1979 (Shōwa 54).<ref>Yodo Shrine, "[http://www.yodojinja.com/yodojinja/syaden.html About the Shrine - Yodo Shrine, Guardian of Fushimi, Kyoto]" (Accessed October 13, 2013)</ref>
The shrine building is surrounded by a [[:en:Tamagaki|tamagaki]] (sacred fence). There is no {{ill|saisenbako|ja|賽銭箱|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/saisenbako|qq=}} (offering box).
The enshrined deity is Yuki-no-Mikura-no-Kami (由貴御倉神), who serves as the guardian deity of Yuki-no-Mikura.<ref name="ic"/><ref name="gk"/>
== Access == ; To Uji Bridge * About 15 minutes by [[:en:Mie Kotsu|Mie Kotsu]] bus from the south exit of [[:en:Iseshi Station|Ise-shi Station]] (JR side) on the [[:en:Sangū Line|Sangū Line]] or from {{ill|Ujiyamada Station|ja|Ujiyamada Station|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ujiyamada Station|qq=}} on the [[:en:Yamada Line (Kintetsu)|Kintetsu Yamada Line]]/{{ill|Kintetsu Toba Line|ja|Toba Line|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kintetsu Toba Line|qq=}}. Get off at the "Naikū-mae" bus stop (final stop).<ref name="mkr">Mie Prefecture Tourism Federation, "[http://www.kankomie.or.jp/spot/detail_2937.html Ise Grand Shrine (Inner Shrine) Information - Visit Mie]" (Accessed October 12, 2013)</ref> * Alternatively, from [[:en:Isuzugawa Station|Isuzugawa Station]] on the Kintetsu Toba Line, take a Mie Kotsu bus to Naikū-mae. * About 5 minutes south via {{ill|Mie Prefectural Route 32|ja|三重県道32号伊勢磯部線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mie Prefectural Route 32|qq=}} (Omikemichi) from {{ill|Ise-nishi IC|ja|伊勢西インターチェンジ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ise-nishi IC|qq=}} on the [[:en:Ise Expressway|Ise Expressway]], or about 5 minutes south via [[:en:Japan National Route 23|National Route 23]] from {{ill|Ise IC|ja|伊勢インターチェンジ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ise IC|qq=}}. Parking is available nearby.<ref name="mkr"/>
; From Uji Bridge * From Uji Bridge, proceed along the approach path towards the Inner Shrine (Main Shrine), and you will find the Gojōden.<ref name="ic"/> Two subordinate shrines are located to the north: Yuki-no-Mikura is on the right, and {{ill|Misakadono-no-Kami|ja|御酒殿神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Misakadono-no-Kami|qq=}} is on the left.<ref name="ic"/><ref name="gk"/> Nearby is the sacred site of {{ill|Yotsuishi-no-Kami|ja|四至神|1=Miyanomeguri-no-Kami|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yotsuishi-no-Kami|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyanomeguri-no-Kami|qq=}}.<ref name="ic"/> == References == {{Reflist}}
