{{infobox Shinto shrine |name= Yuki-no-Mikura |religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image= [[File:Yuki no Mikura 2.jpg|270px]] |location= {{ill|Ujikan-chō|ja|宇治館町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ujikan-chō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 宇治 (伊勢市)}} 1, [[:en:Ise, Mie|Ise, Mie]], [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]], within the precincts of the {{ill|Kōtai Jingū|ja|皇大神宮|1=Kōtai Jingū|2=ja|3=皇大神宮|4=zh|5=皇大神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} |latitude_deg = 34 |latitude_min = 27 |latitude_sec = 19.5 |longitude_deg = 136 |longitude_min = 43 |longitude_sec = 26.6 |map= Japan Mie |enshrined_deity= Yuki-no-Mikura-no-Kami |status= {{ill|Kōtai Jingū|ja|皇大神宮|1=Kōtai Jingū|2=ja|3=皇大神宮|4=zh|5=皇大神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} subordinate shrine |established= Before [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] 23 (804) |main_hall_style= [[Yuiitsu Shinmei-zukuri]] |alternate_names= |sacred_sites= |annual_festival= |rituals= [[:en:Kannamesai Festival|Kannamesai]] }}
'''Yuki-no-Mikura''' (由貴御倉) is a subordinate shrine of {{ill|Ise Grand Shrine (Inner Shrine)|ja|皇大神宮|1=Kōtai Jingū|2=ja|3=皇大神宮|4=zh|5=皇大神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ise Grand Shrine (Inner Shrine)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} (Kōtai Jingū). It is also referred to as '''Yuki-no-Mikura-no-Kami''' (由貴御倉神).<ref name="ic">Ise Bunka-sha (2008): p. 115</ref><ref>Ujiyamada City Office (1929): p. 16</ref><ref name="gs2">Sakurai (1970): p. 156</ref> It is located within the precincts of the Inner Shrine, standing north of the {{ill|Gojōden|ja|五丈殿|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gojōden|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, alongside {{ill|Misakadono-no-Kami|ja|御酒殿神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Misakadono-no-Kami|qq=}}.<ref name="ic"/>
== Overview == Yuki-no-Mikura is located in Ujikan-chō, [[:en:Ise, Mie|Ise, Mie]], within the precincts of the Inner Shrine. It is Ranked 7th among the 30 shrines under the jurisdiction of the Inner Shrine. The term "Yuki" (由貴) in its name means "pure and free from defilement."<ref name="gk">Gakken Publishing (2013): p. 56</ref>
Yuki-no-Mikura was originally a storehouse for offering sacred provisions ({{ill|minie|ja|御贄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/minie|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) used in the {{ill|Yuki-no-Ōmike|ja|由貴大御饌|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yuki-no-Ōmike|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ceremony.<ref name="ic"/><ref name="gk"/> The former shrine building served as a temporary main hall for {{ill|Yodo Shrine|ja|與杼神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yodo Shrine|qq=}} in [[:en:Fushimi-ku, Kyoto|Fushimi-ku, Kyoto]], [[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto]], after the shrine was destroyed by fire, from 1975 (Shōwa 50) to 1979 (Shōwa 54).<ref>Yodo Shrine, "[http://www.yodojinja.com/yodojinja/syaden.html About the Shrine - Yodo Shrine, Guardian of Fushimi, Kyoto]" (Accessed October 13, 2013)</ref>
The shrine building is surrounded by a [[:en:Tamagaki|tamagaki]] (sacred fence). There is no {{ill|saisenbako|ja|賽銭箱|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/saisenbako|qq=}} (offering box).
The enshrined deity is Yuki-no-Mikura-no-Kami (由貴御倉神), who serves as the guardian deity of Yuki-no-Mikura.<ref name="ic"/><ref name="gk"/>
